On occasion it would be highly useful to be able to change DHIS2 internal logging levels on the fly without having to stop, reconfigure, and restart the server.

Sometimes there is an abnormal condition on a production server that we would like to learn more about. Indeed, just the act of restarting the server might clear the problem.

We request three features:

1. A WebAPI GET request, available for superusers only, that returns in alphabetical order all the current loggers in the system, and the current level of each. We understand there are currently between 800 and 900 loggers in the running system. The request could return the following format, or its equivalent:

{code:java}[
    {
        "name": "Hibernate Types",
        "level": "WARN"
    },
    {
        "name": "com.mchange.v1.db.sql.ConnectionUtils",
        "level": "WARN"
    },
    {
        "name": "com.mchange.v2.async.ThreadPoolAsynchronousRunner",
        "level": "WARN"
    },
    ...
]{code}

2. A WebAPI PUT request, also available for superusers only, that allows the user to specify a fully-qualified logger name (as returned in the above GET statement) and a valid log level (e.g., "WARN", "INFO", "ERROR", etc.). The logger would be set to that level, and a response returned that indicates whether or not the operation succeeded.

3. A way to disable or enable the above two features in the dhis.conf file. (A single setting to turn both features on or off would suffice, or it could be a setting that also allows the GET without the PUT in addition to both on or both off.)

A case could be made either way as to whether the feature should default to "on" or "off". We believe that many support people would like this feature on by default if the installation has not taken the extra step to configure this one way or the other. To best support these support people, we recommend that the feature be set to "on" by default.
